
[1]potstone

   POT'STONE, n. Potstone appears to be indurated black talck, passing
   into serpentine. It has a curved and undulatingly lamellar structure,
   passing into slaty.

   Potstone is of a greenish gray color. It occurs massive, or in granular
   concretions.

   Potstone is a variety of steatite.
